 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Software Engineer II Microsoft Bellevue, WA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Are you looking for an opportunity to solve business-critical problems for both internal and external customers using cutting-edge natural language technology? Do you enjoy tackling technical challenges and producing innovative solutions to real-world problems? Then come join the Cognitive Services language team in Microsoft. 
Our team does is responsible for building out a framework and internal platform that supports use case specific customization of natural language models for a variety of language tasks. The services and components are used by multiple Cognitive Services language products. 
Responsibilities 
We are looking for a passionate, creative, driven individual who thrives in a start-up-like environment. We are seeking the best & brightest talent to help drive forward our overall impact in the space of Natural Language and Artificial intelligence. As an engineer, you will contribute to building and optimizing services and infrastructure to specialize custom language models using customer specific data for various common language tasks. We are looking for a candidate with background computer science, natural language processing, machine learning, math, or systems engineering. 
Qualifications 
Required Qualifications: 
2+ years of software development experience (C#, C++ or Python). 
1+ years of experience in cloud services development. 
Preferred Qualifications: 
Experience with Azure Cognitive Services 
Experience with Azure Machine Learning or machine learning techniques 
Excellent technical problem solving, design, coding and debugging skills as evidenced by prior projects. Proficiency in design and implementation of algorithms and architectures. 
Experience in dealing with ambiguity, and to handle changes in customer requirements. 
BS/MS degree in Computer Science or a related discipline. 
